rio is not ruled out,\neven for the brightest type Iax supernovae. Our analysis does not indicate the\nejecta cannot be layered to some degree, but observations within days of\nexplosion are necessary to determine the extent to which the outer ejecta could\nbe layered.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 23 Oct 2021 20:29:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-17"}
